	   <tr><td colspan=2>HP, Mana and resists on the talismans are nice, but mana preservation III is even nicer.<br><br>I have it on my paladin, using it over pieces with more HP and more mana.<br>I don't use spells full time like a pure caster does, and still the effect is noticable.<br>Depending on your mana pool it saves you 200-400 mana, enough for 1 extra spell and by saving the mana and not adding it, it also reduces your med time.<br>A neck piece with 200 pure mana would also mean that you have to med 200 mana more to get from oom to FM, mana preservation means you get more mana to cast and the same med time from oom to FM (or anything in between).<br>As long as you don't have mana preservation in another slot, I'd use it over any other neckpiece, especially as caster but also as hybrid.<br>&nbsp;<br>57 Knight<br>49 Chanter</td></tr>
